at least 1,000,000,000 Ev (1 Gev) . At this energy level the protons will travel at 94% of the velocity of light.<br>
This is about 282,000,000 meters/sec.<br>
To produce nuclear fusion : protons,  deuterons, or tritons must collide with each other at about 10,000 kilometers/sec which is about 3.34 % of the velocity of light.<br>
This is  10,000,000 meters/sec.<br>
That is why nuclear  fusion requires 50,000,000 C to 100,000,000 C or more in temperature to occurr.<br>
 The charged nuclea must have this much kinetic energy to overcome their natural electrostatic repulsion, and fuse together to  build another atomic nucleus (nuclear fusion) <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#484848><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub97.ezboard.com/bnuclearspace.showUserPublicProfile?gid=karov>karov</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Space Tourist</span><br>  Posts: 10<br> <font color=#6F6F6F>(5/31/03 5:10 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub97.ezboard.com/fnuclearspacefrm4.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=330.topic&index=17>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Antiproton asisted impact fussion</span><hr size=1> Do we have an idea about the possibility of shaping electromagnetically the annihilation explosion, so the debris moving with velocity much more than the necesary for causing fusion to be used more efficiently?<br>
